<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-317-257  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 317 257.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Feb 6 1989 v35 n1744 pS12(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>China taking arms merchant role; third world sales fund buys ofWest's military tech. (Special Report on Military Electronics)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ehrlich, Paul Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>China sells Third World countries weaponry, oftenless-sophisticated tanks, planes and other hardware first made inthe 1960s, and uses the profits to purchase upgraded avionics andother Western military technology in order to enhance its militarydefenses.andP;  China's Military Commission head Deng Xiaopingemphasizes upgrading and expanding the country's arms exportindustry as a method for earning foreign exchange required topurchase more advanced US and other Western technology tomodernize China's army, air force and navy.andP;  The CongressionalResearch Service estimated that China's total arms sales to allThird World countries reached nearly $7.3 billion between 1979 and1986.andP;  Western observers estimate that China now exportsapproximately $2 billion worth of weapons annually.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ChinaExportWeaponsMilitary.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>